Choose a hero to begin your journey.

Your name is Olberic, and you are a warrior.

Once a proud knight, you lost both king and kingdom in a bloody coup.
Today, you serve as a master-at-arms for a remote mountain village.

"To what end do I swing my blade?"
The question tortured you night after restless night.
Then, one day, you overhear a name from your past, giving you new purpose...

Your name is Tressa, and you are a merchant.

You stock the shelves at your parents' shop in your sleepy, seaside hometown.
Yet you often find yourself gazing out at sea, longing for something more.
"What lies beyond the horizon?"
You thought you'd never know the answer.
Then, one day, an unfamiliar vessel weighs anchor at the docks,
changing your life forever...

Your name is Cyrus, and you are a scholar.

You teach at the Royal Academy in Atlasdam, and though you have
numerous admirers, your only true passion is the pursuit of knowledge.

"There is so much more I would learn!"
One day, you realize that an invaluable tome
has vanished from the Royal Library,
piquing your insatiable curiosity...

Your name is Primrose, and you are a dancer.

You ply your trade in the pleasure district of Sunshade,
a town forever shrouded in darkness.

In truth, you are the highborn daughter of the once-proud House Azelhart,
an identity you conceal from all.
"Three men bearing the mark of the crow. They took my father from me."
But you will have your revenge...

Your name is H'aanit, and you are a hunter.

One of the last descendants of an ancient clan that calls the deep forest home,
your prowess with the bow is unmatched.
Your master left home one year ago, summoned to hunt a dread beast,
and you protected the village while awaiting his return.
Then, one day, the return of an old friend gives you cause for concern,
and you strike out on a journey of your own.

Your name is Therion, and you are a thief.

While your past is a guarded secret, your exploits are known far and wide.
Mere whispers of your extravagant heists strike fear into the hearts of the wealthy.

Drifting into the Cliftlands one day, you hear a rumor of great riches to be had.
You set your sights on a mansion said to be impregnable,
only to find what you never expected...

Your name is Ophilia, and you are a cleric.

You hail from the snowswept Frostlands, where you dutifully serve the
Order of the Flame under your adoptive father, the archbishop.

As your adoptive sister—and best friend—prepares to embark on a
perilous pilgrimage, you stand ever at her side.
But unbeknownst to the both of you, events are about to take a tragic turn...

Your name is Alfyn, and you are an apothecary.

You treat the wounded and sick in a small village
amid the babbling brooks of the Riverlands.
Stricken ill as a child, you were saved by a traveler who asked for
nothing in return, inspiring you to follow in his footsteps.
Though hesitant to leave the only home you've known, your best friend
convinces you to follow your dream, wherever it may lead you...

Tips for the Traveler: Part I

The damage you deal with physical attacks is based upon the physical attack value of your currently held weapon. The damage you deal with magic attacks is based on the weapon equipped with the highest magical attack value. Certain weapons will increase a damage type by a percentage, these weapons will always increase damage as listed even when not being held.

Many equippable items will increase a character's stats or benefit them in other ways. A weapon will only effectively increase a stat when held, except magic attack which always uses the highest value as previously mentioned. Armor, helmets, off-hand equipment and accessories will always increase stats as listed. Percentile increases stack additively up to a max of 100%.

Each point of physical or magical defense will mitigate damage taken of the appropriate type. The defense is first halved, and then weighed against the attacker's attacking stat. A similar operation is done to determine hit rate, where accuracy is weighed against evasion. Speed is weighed against critical and reduces a character's chances of being crit.

The potency of a player character's healing abilities is based on the user's base magical defense stat. Buffing one's magical defense or having it be debuffed will not change their healing potency. Fixed damage such as soulstones is not increased by stats, but can be increased by percentile elemental damage amp.
Tips for the Traveler: Part II

Steal can only be used effectively in towns after patrol patterns for that town are obtained. You may obtain the patrol patterns needed for each town by going through their closest chapter dungeon. Even after patrol patterns are obtained, items which are worth 10,000 leaves or more cannot be stolen. Scrutinize and Inquire do not offer much in terms of material gain, so don't use them left and right unless you're generally interested in an NPC's life. Lastly, note that all capture beasts obtained outside of H'aanit's starting roster have 99 uses.

Try talking to the hint hounds spread throughout the game, especially within Chapter 1 settlements. If you encounter an issue that prevents you from progressing, post on this mod's Nexus page or contact Beepo on the Team Asano Modding discord.

Your name is Olberic, and you are a swordsman in the small village of Cobbleston.
You arrive at Victors Hollow. Among the voices discussing the upcoming tournament, you overhear the name "Gustav"...
After learning what you can from Gustav, you head to Wellspring. Erhardt should be here somewhere...
You make your way to Riverford where you hope to find the mercenary Werner, the man behind the fall of Hornburg.
Your name is Primrose, and you are a dancer in the town of Sunshade.
The trail of the Left-hand Man leads you to Stillsnow. Hoping to find clues on his whereabouts, you take a walk through town...
Heeding the words of the dying crow, you have come home to Noblecourt, where you hope to find the truth that has eluded you for so long...
You have come to Everhold in pursuit of Simeon, who revealed himself as the ringleader of the crows. Here, you soon find that the stage has already been set...
Your name is Cyrus, and you are a scholar at the Royal Academy in Atlasdam.
Hoping to solve the mysteries behind a certain ancient tome, you head to Quarrycrest. Here, you seek out Odette, a former colleague who may be able to shed some light on the matter.
You make your way to Stonegard after learning that the original copy of the tome you seek might be there. But you can't help but feel that someone's been watching you...
Still in pursuit of the forbidden tome, you journey to Duskbarrow and ever closer to the truth...
Your name is H'aanit, and you are a hunter living in S'warkii with your loyal snow leopard Linde.
You travel to Stonegard, where your master, Z'aanta, was headed when he penned his first and only letter. And so your search begins...
In hopes of undoing your master's petrification, you head to Stillsnow to meet the seer Susanna.
You arrive in Marsalim. With an idea of Redeye's whereabouts and a means to avoid petrification, you prepare to face the beast...
Your name is Ophilia, and you are a cleric at the cathedral in Flamesgrace.
The first stop on your pilgrimage is the town of Saintsbridge, where a memorable meeting awaits you...
From Saintsbridge, you head to Goldshore to perform the Kindling once more. There, you encounter a familiar face...
You follow Lianna and the ember to the town of Wispermill, where the Savior awaits...
Your name is Tressa and you are a merchant in the small port town of Rippletide.
Following in the footsteps of the nameless author, you find yourself in a Quarrycrest very different than the one he described. Your search for business begins here...
After learning of the Merchants' Fair, you head to Victors Hollow to find an item worthy of the auction. Eventually, you make your way to one of the shops...
You arrive in Grandport, which is abuzz with excitement over the auction. It is there you finally realize what your true treasure is...
Your name is Therion, and you are a thief who drifted into Bolderfall.
Arriving at Noblecourt in search of the ruby dragonstone, you quickly overhear a rumor that a scholar in town is using the stone to conduct some questionable research...
Your search for the emerald stone brings you to Wellspring. You decide to sneak into the black market to see if the treasure you seek lies within...
You arrive in Northreach, a town under Darius's control. Still, you are determined to retrieve the emerald and gold dragonstones.
Your name is Alfyn, and you are an apothecary in the small town of Clearbrook.
Your travels have brought you to Goldshore, where a fever is running rampant. You roll up your sleeves and begin to get to work...
You arrive in Saintsbridge to see a man and an apothecary speaking. Whether this meeting augurs good fortune or ill remains to be seen...
Your journey as an apothecary has carried you to Orewell. Your confidence shaken, you pray that this is where you will find the answers you seek...

Only the headmaster and the guard possess keys to the special archives.
He knows the value of tomes, and is burdened with debt, to boot.
He has a key, yes. Yet he knows little of the true value of the books he guards.
He has a key, this is true, but the dust gathered upon it suggests he has not used it lately.
Rumor has it that all of the people who went missing have been seen walking near the inn.
The disappearances have been happening both in broad daylight and in the dead of night.
It would appear there is an entrance to the sewers behind the inn.
He has closed himself off to the world since losing his dear daughter.
Fifteen years ago, he lacked the coin to pay for the medicine his child so desperately needed.
He harbors deep regrets having taken on this job for the money.
It would appear the twelve gods sealed off the power beyond the edge of the world.
The forbidden power of the gods has been likened to a golden fruit.
It is filled with arcane knowledge on the secrets of life and death.
